org.apache.james.mime4j.message
Class MessageWriter

java.lang.Object
  org.apache.james.mime4j.message.MessageWriter

public class MessageWriter
extends java.lang.Object

Writes a message (or a part of a message) to an output stream.

This class cannot be instantiated; instead the three static instances STRICT_ERROR, STRICT_IGNORE or LENIENT implement different strategies for encoding header fields and preamble and epilogue of a multipart.

This class can also be subclassed to implement custom strategies for writing messages.

Field Summary
static MessageWriter LENIENT
          A message writer that uses the charset of the Content-Type header for encoding.
static MessageWriter STRICT_ERROR
          A message writer that uses US-ASCII for encoding and throws MimeIOException if a non ASCII character is encountered.
static MessageWriter STRICT_IGNORE
          A message writer that uses US-ASCII for encoding but ignores non ASCII characters.
